#### summaries of summaries

#### chapter 18

chapter 18 talked about Ethics Theories and practices. the 2 Theories that was talked about was the Consequentialism and the Deontological Theory. the Deontological theory believes that there should be a moral law that determine what's ethical, as pointed out in the text there are some flaws with this Theory. the Deontological theory don't allow for any rules to be broken and if there is conflict with two different rules there isn't any solution. the Consequentialism theory is base of the result of your actions, if your actions made more people happy then it make people sad then it was ethical. the book also talked about Ethical Discussion making by first finding the problem and make some kind of pros and cons list. 
